projects.description:
Responsible for the organisation and coordination of a 10-day PFM introduction training for a group of 25 government officials working in public finance management from south East Europe (Bosnia, Serbia, Montenegro, Turkey, Kosovo, Macedonia). This training was financed by the Netherlands Ministry of Foreign Affairs and facilitated by Ecorys. The training aimed to learn lessons from good practices in the Dutch system of Public Finance Management.
Main responsibilities: 
- Development and preparation  of  the overall training program
- Lead organiser: identifying and instructing  lecturers, arranging study visits, collecting training materials and setup of an e-learning environment;
- Preparation of training material on the Dutch budget cycle;
- Provided the training session on the Budge Cycle and budget preparation.

profile_positions.description:
As a consultant in the International Development unit of Ecorys, I am mainly working on:
-   Acquisition and implementation of Public Finance Management assignments - topics include accountability and auditing, taxation and local governance;
-   Implementation of evaluations of development projects and programmes of international organisations - clients incude IMF, IFC, UNICEF, EU;
- Organisation and development of PFM training courses and study tours.

International work experiences in Latin America (Peru), Africa (Kenya, Rwanda, Tanzania), Middle East (Lebanon, Palestine), Asia & Pacific (Australia, New Zealand, Pakistan, Samoa, Solomon Islands, Tonga, Vanuatu).
